entry.def: If you unroll something such as a sheet of paper or cloth, or if it unrolls, it opens up and becomes flat when it was previously rolled in a cylindrical shape.

example.ex: I unrolled my sleeping bag as usual...
example.tran: 我像往常一样铺开我的睡袋。

example.ex: Guests bring movies on tape, and show them on the screen that unrolls from the ceiling.
example.tran: 客人带来了录影带，并在从天花板上放下来的幕布上放映。

means.word_mean: 1. extended or spread out fully before one;

sentences.sentence: "saw miles of sand dunes rolled out to the horizon"

means.word_mean: 2. unwound and spread out (of something rolled or coiled)
